///
main.seen — User-facing CLI entry point for the Seen compiler

Pipeline stage: Entry point (before all compilation stages)
Input: Command-line arguments (subcommand + flags)
Output: Dispatches to the appropriate compilation pipeline

This is the production compiler binary's main(). It parses CLI arguments and
routes to one of several compilation paths:
  - "build"  → LLVM backend (default) or C backend via main_compiler.seen
  - "run"    → Compile to temp file + execute
  - "check"  → Frontend only (lexer → parser → typechecker), no codegen
  - "fmt"    → Basic source formatter (indent normalization)
  - "init"   → Project scaffolding
  - "import-c" → Generate Seen extern bindings from C headers
  - "pkg"    → Package workflow for fetch/pack/publish

The LLVM backend path delegates to StageCompileSeenProgram (main_compiler.seen),
which handles multi-module IR generation, optimization, and linking.
The C backend path uses CGenerator for a simpler gcc-based pipeline.

Multi-language support: --language flag selects keyword set (en/ar/es/ru/zh/ja),
passed through to the lexer's KeywordManager.
///

